# OpenClaw configuration.
# Local: copy to .env and fill in real values — `cp .env.example .env`.
# Dokploy: set these in the app's Environment Settings, not a committed file.
# Never commit .env. Docs: https://docs.openclaw.ai
#
# The official image is config-file-driven: only secrets + a little infra live here.
# Model, channels, tools.deny and agent defaults live in openclaw.json (see
# openclaw.example.json). Keep this file small.

# --- Provider (set at least one) ---
# If the official image expects provider keys in openclaw.json / an auth profile
# instead of env, move them there and drop these.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# --- Gateway ---
# Shared token for the gateway. It is the ONLY auth boundary in front of the Control
# UI (there is no nginx / basic auth). Required. Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=
# NOTE: the gateway bind is NOT an env var — set it in openclaw.json as
# `gateway.bind: "lan"` so the gateway listens beyond loopback and Docker can forward
# the host-loopback-published port (127.0.0.1:18789). Host exposure stays loopback-only.
# The Control UI is served by the gateway on port 18789 and reached over an SSH tunnel:
#   ssh -N -L 18789:127.0.0.1:18789 user@YOUR_HOST   # then open http://localhost:18789
# First connect needs a one-time device pairing. Inside the container run
# "openclaw devices list", then "openclaw devices approve <id>". You also paste
# OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN into the Control UI settings to authenticate the session.
